This paper discusses the optimization problem behind deep neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the structure of the network, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the activation function, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the number of hidden units and the network structure, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
